# ADR-0011 — keep manifests + vocab TSVs committed, skip the binary
# checkpoints. Each backbone produced by Phase 1 / Phase 2 is a
# ~750MB-1.1GB model.safetensors that would blow git's per-file cap.
#
# What stays committed:
#   - vocab_extension_manifest.json
#   - vocab_candidates.tsv
#   - mlm_training_manifest.json
#   - any *.json / *.tsv / *.md companion files
#
# What is ignored:
#   - model.safetensors
#   - tokenizer.json (it's ~17 MB — fine to skip; rebuildable from
#                    base + vocab_candidates.tsv via
#                    scripts/_extend_reranker_tokenizer.py)
#   - sentencepiece.bpe.model
#   - any per-epoch HF Trainer checkpoint state
#   - checkpoints/

model.safetensors
tokenizer.json
sentencepiece.bpe.model
checkpoints/
*.bin
*.pt
optimizer.pt
scheduler.pt
rng_state.pth
scaler.pt
